The paper discusses the role of Formal Methods in System Engineering, which is a topic that falls under the category of Software Engineering (cs.SE). The paper also presents two analysis techniques based on solid mathematical theories, which suggests that the paper could also belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) categories. The techniques are also related to modeling and analysis, which could place the paper in the Mathematical Software (cs.MA) category. Finally, the paper discusses the development of software tools, which could suggest that it belongs to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category.
